  "texts": [
    "Despite being limited by the effectiveness of textual JBPs, our method achieves decent performance with different JBPs and even sometimes higher ASR than its textual counterpart (i.e., ASR hypo-ours =83.5% vs. ASR hypo-text =48.5%).",
    "While textual JBP theoretically bounds attack success, ImgTrojan's superior ASR performance stems from exploiting unique cross-modal interactions.",
    "This unexpected finding reveals novel attack vectors unavailable to purely text-based approaches, warranting further investigation in our ongoing research.",
    "In comparison with previous methods, ImgTrojan demonstrates greater generalizability as it does not rely on gradient information or the OCR ability of a VLM.",
    "As shown in Table 3 and Figures 3a and 3b, we apply ImgTrojan to LLaVA-v1.5 7B."
  ],
